STATE of Missouri, Respondent,
v.
Keeley SMASHEY, Appellant. No. ED 105485 Missouri Court of Appeals, Eastern District, NORTHERN DIVISION. Filed: June 26, 2018
Motion for Rehearing and/or Transfer to Supreme Court Denied July 31, 2018
Application for Transfer Denied October 30, 2018 Johnathan S. Hoover, 201 North Third Street, Suite 301, Hannibal, MO 63401, for appellant. Garreth Cooksey, Robert E. Rapp, 906 Broadway, Room 7, Hannibal, MO 63401, for respondent. Before James M. Dowd, C.J., Lawrence E. Mooney., J., and Colleen Dolan, J.

ORDER

PER CURIAM

Keeley Smashey appeals the judgment entered on a jury verdict finding her guilty of third-degree assault of a law-enforcement officer, in violation of Section 565.083. No jurisprudential purpose would be served by a written opinion. We have furnished the parties with a memorandum, for their information only, setting forth the reasons for our order. We affirm. Rule 30.25(b).
